It’s just April but many celebrities have already got engaged. Here are a five Nigerian celebrities who got engaged so far in 2022: 1. Kemi Adetiba  The 42-year-old producer got engaged to the love of her life, Oscar Heman-Ackah on the 28th January, 2022 while she was on vacation in Ghana. The movies she produced and directed include King of boys and The wedding party 2. Seyi Shay  Deborah Oluwaseyi Joshua, fondly called Seyi Shay, confirmed being engaged in an interview with Beat Fm January 2022. The singer is expecting a baby. 3. Rita Dominic   Ex-Miss World Uganda launches foundation to keep girls in…     I can only marry a financially stable man, Carolyna…     Marriage? Count me out, says Iyabo Ojo    The veteran actressrecently announced her engagement with Daily Times publisher, Fidelis Anosike. 4. Temi Otedola    The billionaire heiress, Temi Otedola who has been in relationship with the Ghanaian musician, Mr Eazi recently got engaged on April 10, 2022 5. Tim Godfrey    The gospel singer announced his engagement on February 16, 2022 via Instagram and wrote: “Thank you for saying YES! I can’t imagine how I’ve lived without you all my life. But guess what? I would have waited forever till we crossed paths. But thank God, this blissful and Heaven-made journey has started. “After giving my life to Christ, sharing life with you is the best thing that has happened to me. No measure of time with you will be enough but let’s start with forever. “‘EKJ’ You are my STILL WATERS! I love you.”